edu.uconn.cse.adder

Class AdderInteger

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.uconn.cse.adder.AdderInteger
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable

    public class AdderInteger
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable
    Arbitrary-precision integers for modular arithmetic. Internally, Java's BigInteger class is used to represent the value and the modulus.
    Since:
    0.0.1
    See Also:
    BigInteger

        public static AdderInteger safePrime(int bitLength)

        public int compareTo(java.lang.Object b)
        Compares this AdderInteger with the specified AdderInteger. This method is provided in preference to individual methods for each of the six boolean comparison operators (<, ==, >, >=, !=, <=). The suggested idiom for performing these comparisons is: (x.compareTo(y) <op> 0), where <op> is one of the six comparison operators.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable
        Parameters:
        b - AdderInteger to which this AdderInteger is to be compared.
        Returns:
        -1, 0 or 1 as this BigInteger is numerically less than, equal to, or greater than b
